debugger-inspector — Phase 4: the inspector (pages, accessors, path, workspace)
================================================================================

See also:
  clautolisp/documentation/clautolisp-debugger-implementation-plan.org (Phase 4)
  clautolisp/documentation/clautolisp-debugger-spec.org (Part IV: §14–§16)
  issues/open/debugger-snapshot-stepping.issue (uses snapshot values)

Context
-------

The inspector is a SEPARATE library from the debugger (the debugger uses it
to display values, but it is also usable from any REPL, attached or not). It
is a generic value browser that tracks the ORIGIN of the inspected value and
the NAVIGATION PATH from origin to the current value, so the user can
reconstruct accessor expressions or save references.

Scope / deliverables
--------------------

1. New system `clautolisp/autolisp-inspect`, package `clautolisp.inspect`:
   - `(inspect value &key into origin) -> inspector-session`.
   - `inspector-session` ops: current, history, page, origin, down, up, eval,
     path-expression, bind (spec §14).

2. `inspect-page-for` generic (spec §15) + per-type methods and accessors for
   every AutoLISP type: numbers, strings (`(substr _ n 1)`), symbols, cons /
   list (`(car _)`, `(cdr _)`, `(nth n _)`), ename (`(cdr (assoc g (entget _)))`),
   selection set (`(ssname _ n)`), VLA object (`(vla-get-prop _)`), file
   descriptor (read-only), hash table. Each component: label, preview,
   accessor S-expr, value. Non-AutoLISP-expressible accessors marked :opaque.

3. Path-expression composition (spec §15.2): fold the accessor chain from
   origin; return (values partial :partial) when an :opaque step is crossed.

4. Workspace `$N` (spec §16.2): per-session numbered slots `$1..$N` + `$0`
   alias, in a debugger-private namespace that never touches AutoLISP's symbol
   table; resolved by the debugger eval layer only.

5. `session-bind target` (spec §16.1): :workspace (default) / :global SYMBOL /
   :frame FRAME SYMBOL / :setq SYMBOL, with frame-aware semantics and the
   §16.1 restriction (no NEW frame-local binding mid-execution).

Acceptance
----------

- Inspect an ename, descend into DXF group 10, copy path
  `(cdr (assoc 10 (entget EN)))`, bind to `$4`, then eval `(distance $4 $5)`.
- :opaque descent yields a partial path + offers a workspace binding.
- FiveAM tests; `*version*` bumped.
